description:
Fix the 'Open Test Page' popup - the VAPI voice widget button is not appearing in the bottom-right corner.

The test page HTML needs to properly load and initialize the VAPI widget. Update the generated HTML in the DemoPreview component:

1. Use the correct VAPI widget script that creates a floating button:
   - The widget script URL should be: https://cdn.vapi.ai/widget.js
   - OR use the proper VAPI Web SDK initialization

2. The HTML should include:
   - The VAPI public key: 919bbeaa-d657-4c72-a7b9-8772ac8ebd19
   - The assistant ID (vapi_agent_id from the API)
   - Proper initialization that creates a visible floating button

3. Try this approach for the widget:
   ```html
   <script>
     var vapiInstance = null;
     (function(d, t) {
       var g = d.createElement(t), s = d.getElementsByTagName(t)[0];
       g.src = "https://cdn.vapi.ai/widget.js";
       g.defer = true;
       g.async = true;
       s.parentNode.insertBefore(g, s);
       g.onload = function() {
         vapiInstance = window.vapiSDK.run({
           apiKey: "919bbeaa-d657-4c72-a7b9-8772ac8ebd19",
           assistant: "ASSISTANT_ID_HERE",
           config: {
             position: "bottom-right",
             offset: "40px",
             width: "50px",
             height: "50px"
           }
         });
       }
     })(document, "script");
   </script>
   ```

4. Or use the simpler embed approach:
   ```html
   <script
     src="https://cdn.vapi.ai/widget.js"
     data-public-key="919bbeaa-d657-4c72-a7b9-8772ac8ebd19"
     data-assistant-id="ASSISTANT_ID_HERE">
   </script>
   ```

5. Make sure the popup window stays open and the widget actually renders as a floating button in the bottom-right corner that users can click to start voice chat.

Test with the actual assistant ID from the API response.
